 Section 102 of the Food, Agriculture, Conservation, and Trade Act of 1990 provides that no State shall provide for
(and no person shall collect, directly or indirectly) a greater allowance for the processing of milk (``make allowance'')
than is permitted under a Federal program to establish a Grade A price for manufacturing butter, nonfat dry milk, or
cheese. 
