The FAA is considering an amendment to part 71 of the Federal Aviation Regulations (14 CFR part 71) to modify Class D
airspace at Roswell, NM. The current Class D airspace at Roswell Industrial Air Center, NM, was modified by rulemaking
action dated December 12, 1993 (58 FR 63885). That modification included an extension of the Class D airspace within
3.7 miles each side of the Chisum Very High Omni-Directional Radio Range/Tactical Air Navigation (VORTAC) 290
<!-- PJG 0017 degreeslatlong -->
&cir; radial extending from the 5.0-mile radius to 14.8 miles northwest of the airport. That extension to the Class
