<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Each State, in cooperation with its political subdivisions, should have a comprehensive program to promote motorcycle
safety. To be effective in reducing the number of motorcycle crash deaths and injuries, State programs should address
the use of helmet and other protective gear, proper licensing, impaired riding, rider training, conspicuity, and
motorist awareness. This Motorcycle Safety Program Guideline will assist States and local communities in the development
and implementation of effective motorcycle safety programs.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=84 g=1 f=1 -->
I. Program Management
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
