<!-- PJG ITAG l=21 g=1 f=1 -->
Source of program funding;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
State organization to administer the program;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Use of Motorcycle Safety Foundation curriculum or equivalent State-approved curriculum;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Reasonable availability of rider education courses for all interested residents of legal riding age;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Instructor training and certification;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Incentives for successful course completion such as licensing skills test exemption;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Quality control of the program;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Ability to purchase insurance for the program;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Permission to spend money in other motorcycle safety program areas as deemed appropriate;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
State guidelines for conduct of the program; and Program evaluation.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
