with price and any required technical and management proposals, unless the offeror submits a previously-approved
commercial products plan. Maximum practicable utilization of small, small disadvantaged, and women-owned small
business concerns as subcontractors is a matter of national interest with both social and economic benefits. It is
the General Services Administration's (GSA's) expectation that an offeror's subcontracting plan will reflect
a commitment to assuring that small, small disadvantaged, and women-owned small business concerns are provided
the maximum practicable opportunity, consistent with efficient contract performance, to participate as subcontractors
in the performance of the resulting contract.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
