<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Background 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The Secretary is proposing to revise 34 CFR part 682 to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
implement changes made to the HEA by the Higher Education 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Amendments of 1992 (Pub. L. 102&hyph;325), enacted July 23, 1992, as 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
well as certain changes added by Public Law 103&hyph;208, enacted 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
December 20, 1993. These regulations seek to improve the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
efficiency of federal student aid programs, and, by so doing, to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
improve their capacity to enhance opportunities for postsecondary 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
education. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=84 g=1 f=1 -->
Summary of Comments From Regional Meetings 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
In compliance with section 492(a) of the HEA, the Secretary 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
convened regional meetings during September 1992 to obtain public 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
involvement in the development of proposed regulations. The 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
purpose of the meetings was to ``provide for a comprehensive 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
discussion and exchange of information concerning the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
implementation'' of certain parts of Public Law 102&hyph;325. In 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
addition, attendees at the regional meetings were asked to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
nominate individuals to act as negotiators in the negotiated 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
rulemaking process required by section 492(b) of the HEA. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
The regional meetings were conducted for two days each in 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
San Francisco, California; New York, New York; Atlanta, Georgia; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
and Kansas City, Missouri. Each participant at the regional 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
meetings was assigned to one of six groups which were asked to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
discuss particular issue areas identified by the Department. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Each group at the regional meetings prepared a report of its 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
discussion and recommendations and those reports were presented 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
to the Department for consideration during the preparation of the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
proposed regulations. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
The issues addressed in this Notice of Proposed Rulemaking 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
were discussed by one of the groups at each regional meeting. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
The specific recommendations made at those meetings are addressed 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
below. The Secretary considered these comments in preparing 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
draft proposed regulations. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=83 g=1 f=1 -->
1. Loan Discharge for Borrowers Attending Schools That 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Close 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Public Law 102&hyph;325 added section 437(c) to the HEA to provide 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
that loans will be canceled for student borrowers who are unable 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
to complete their program of study because the school closed. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
The specific issues described below were discussed in connection 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
with this section.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->
</SUPPLEM>
