(10) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Administrative Garnishment.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 (i) If a guaranty agency 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
decides to garnish the disposable pay of a borrower who is not 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
making payments on a loan held by the agency, on which the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Secretary has paid a reinsurance claim, it shall do so in 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
accordance with the following procedures: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(A) The employer shall deduct and pay to the agency from a 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
borrower's wages an amount that does not exceed 10 percent of the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
borrower's disposable pay for each pay period, or the amount 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
permitted by 15 U.S.C. 1673, unless the borrower provides the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
agency with written consent to deduct a greater amount. For this 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
purpose, the term ``disposable pay'' means that part of the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
borrower's compensation from an employer remaining after the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
deduction of any amounts required by law to be withheld. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(B) At least 30 days before the initiation of garnishment 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
proceedings, the guaranty agency shall mail to the borrower's 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
last known address, a written notice of the nature and amount of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the debt, the intention of the agency to initiate proceedings to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
collect the debt through deductions from pay, and an explanation 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
of the borrower's rights. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(C) The guaranty agency shall offer the borrower an 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
opportunity to inspect and copy agency records related to the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
debt. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(D) The guaranty agency shall offer the borrower an 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
opportunity to enter into a written repayment agreement with the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
agency under terms agreeable to the agency. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(E) The guaranty agency shall offer the borrower an 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
opportunity for a hearing in accordance with paragraph 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b)(10)(i)(J) of this section concerning the existence or the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
amount of the debt and, in the case of a borrower whose repayment 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
schedule is established other than by a written agreement under 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
paragraph (b)(10)(i)(D) of this section, the terms of the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
repayment schedule. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(F) The guaranty agency shall sue any employer (including a 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
borrower who is self-employed) for any amount that the employer, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
after receipt of the garnishment notice provided by the agency 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
under paragraph (b)(10)(i)(H) of this section, fails to withhold 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
from wages owed and payable to an employee under the employer's 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
normal pay and disbursement cycle. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(G) The guaranty agency may not garnish the wages of a 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
borrower whom it knows has been involuntarily separated from 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
employment until the borrower has been reemployed continuously 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
for at least 12 months. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(H) Unless the guaranty agency receives information that the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
agency believes justifies a delay or cancellation of the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
withholding order, it shall send a withholding order to the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
employer within 20 days after the borrower fails to make a timely 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
request for a hearing, or, if a timely request for a hearing is 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
made by the borrower, within 20 days after a final decision is 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
made by the agency to proceed with garnishment. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(I) The notice given to the employer under paragraph 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b)(10)(i)(H) of this section must contain only the information 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
as may be necessary for the employer to comply with the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
withholding order. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(J) The guaranty agency shall provide a hearing, which, at 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the borrower's option, may be oral or written, if the borrower 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
submits a written request for a hearing on the existence or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
amount of the debt or the terms of the repayment schedule. An 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
oral hearing may, at the borrower's option, be conducted either 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
in-person or by telephone conference. All telephonic charges 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
must be the responsibility of the guaranty agency. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

